  "texts": [
    "Non-invasive AI methods are also capable of assessing morphological features of immotile or frozen sperm that are difficult to characterize manually.",
    "Current viability tests require cytotoxic staining that renders individual spermatozoon unusable for ICSI.",
    "Recently, Jiang et al.",
    "described an AI model capable of identifying viable sperm based on a single bright-field image without the need for any sample processing or reagents 58.",
    "The model exhibited 94.9% accuracy, 97.0% sensitivity, and 93.3% specificity, based on subtle morphological changes to the cell nucleus."
  ],
